general purpose application design:-
    apply OOPs
    SOLID principle  
    low level , high level design
    support systems(call,mail,text,etc..)

4 pillers of OOP :  
    Inheritance - code reusability
    Abstraction
    Polymorphism 
    Encapsulation
    answer -> use example and state why

//person -> George Hodz


Naming Conventions ->
    use proper names

variables -> instance , static and local variables
    - instance : 
        always depends on state of object 
        eg. record of students in college
    - static:
        doesn't depends on object
        created single memory 
        access, modify, delete using ClassName.varname
        eg. college name

methods ->
    class methods 
        to be find
    static methods : 
        no self arguement is passed 
        eg. admission process in college,
    instance methods : 
        uses self as default arguement


Inheritance: code reusability
1. Single Inheritance [BASE -> DERIVED]
2. Multiple Inheritance [BASE -> DERIVED]
3. Multilevel Inheritance [BASE -> DERIVED]

Abstraction : PayTM -> IRCTC ticket booking

Polymorphism: having many forms
    - Compile Time Polymorphism (Static | Early Binding):
        eg. function overloading
        python doesnot support constructor and function overloading
            - 
    - Runtime Polymorphism (Dynamic | Late Binding):
        eg. function overriding

destructor -> deallocates the resources

Garbage collector : (GC module)
GC -> destructor 
destructor -> ack-> GC
GC -> free the memory